	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=12325&amp;mid=103050804422184">ermm...</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=12325&amp;mid=103050804422184#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Aug 28th 12:27 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=134877"><span id=" ">Neomeris</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">43 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.25]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>This belt is really good for most any class. Assuming the mob can drop both at once, would probably be fang to casters and belt to melees. What does a caster do during those fights when they CANT sit down? Well, why not walk up and melee the mob to proc for mana from behind. Nice for a necro who fear kites too I would guess. <br/><br/>IMO this belt would be nice for my warrior. You're basicly looking at a 15 ac, 10 str, 60 hp, +5 sv all belt here for a high level warrior.<br/><br/>This is good for any class really as it'll up your HP and DPS without losing much AC.<br/><br/>To answer before it's said.. is this a monk item? Nope. Would it be good for a monk? Yes.<br/><br/><br/>To the poster who is talking about there is a lot of competition for the waist slot by the time you can get this, like a BoDS or lodi belt... you don't have to be in an uber guild to take out a 400 hitting mob with only 75k hp. We don't have any dorf belts or anything of that quality, but we can gather 30 level 58+ easily.<br/><br/>Just remember not everyone is &quot;uber&quot; just because they have a lot of 60's. This is one of those pre-NToV mobs in my eyes. Good for those guilds that are on the verge of pushing it to that next level.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
